Ember Table  

by Addepar

A fast, lazy rendered, easily extensible table built with Ember.js.

  • View On GitHub

Sort, freeze, resize, and rearrange columns. Collapse and select rows. Freeze headers and footers. Navigate with keyboard.

Getting Started

Compile with grunt:


    $ npm install -g grunt
    $ npm install
    $ grunt
    $ python -m SimpleHTTPServer

Dependencies

  • ember.js
  • jquery-ui
  • jquery.mousewheel.js

Future Work

  • Bug fixes - we are aware that there are bugs. Please help us out by filing github issues or submitting pull requests!
  • Better documentations
  • Unit tests
  • Cell single, multi selection
  • Better column drag and drop
  • Support colspan and rowspan
  • Further performance improvements

Authors & Contributors

ppong, ldevalliere and sherb

With lots of help from the Ember.js team

ebryn, tomdale, wycats

The original idea for lazy rendering was inspired by Erik Bryn.

We keep the ember-table.js code to the minimum necessary, giving users as much control as possible.

The examples above demonstrate how you can extend and customize the table. For further details on the individual examples, refer to the examples directory on github.

TThis project is maintained by Addepar and this Theme was inspired by orderedlist
